Boil a full #kettle{}.

While it comes to the boil, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g},
~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on
high heat. Boil the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g}, ~{4%minutes}.

When cooked, drain and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g} to the beef and mushrooms. Fry until slightly
softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Gochujang Paste{50%g}, @Sweet Chilli Sauce{32%g},
@Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and @Water{50%ml}. Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked noodles. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too
thick.

Share the noodles between your #serving bowls{}.

> Super speedy, these Easy Peasy Korean Style Beef Noodles take only 15 minutes
> to make. The popular Korean condiment gochujang contains chillies,
> fermented soybeans and glutinous rice which give it its savoury-sweet flavour.

